doc.previous: Northwest s meteorologists led by Dan Sowa pioneered the first clear air turbulence forecasting system in 1957 important since the airline flew many northern routes over turbulence prone mountain areas Northwest remains a leader in turbulence prediction providing TPAWS turbulence prediction and warning services to other airlines 14
doc.after: During the postwar regulated era Northwest s domestic network remained focused around the northern transcontinental route through New York Boston Chicago Minneapolis and Seattle Northwest also served Hawaii from the West Coast and Georgia and Florida from Chicago 16 On June 1 1959 Northwest accepted its first turboprop jet aircraft the Lockheed L 188 Electra from its manufacturer Northwest Airlines started flying the three engine Boeing 727 jet airliner in November 1964 when its first short fuselage series 51 was delivered 17 Many examples of the stretched series 251 followed
